# Real-time CIBIL Score Integration Plan

This plan outlines the steps to transition from a simulated CIBIL score experience to a real-time integration using a Credit Bureau API (like Razorpay/Karza or Experian).

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **API Keys & Compliance**: To go live, you will need a business account with a provider (e.g., Razorpay Karza). Real bureau APIs require **Business PAN & GST**.
>
> **Backend Proxy**: We will use **Supabase Edge Functions** to host the API logic. This is CRITICAL to keep your API keys secret and avoid exposing them in the browser.

## Proposed Changes

---

### 1. Backend Integration (Supabase)

We need a secure environment to call the external API.

#### [NEW] `supabase/functions/check-cibil/index.js`
- Acts as a proxy between your app and the Bureau (Karza/Experian).
- Stores the API Key securely in Supabase Environment Variables.
- **Mock Mode**: Initially, it will simulate a successful API response with a realistic delay, allowing you to test the UI flow perfectly.

---

### 2. Frontend Services Layer

#### [NEW] [cibilService.js](file:///c:/Users/bogag/OneDrive/Desktop/Kruthik%20loan/src/services/cibilService.js)
- A dedicated service to handle API communication.
- Methods: `initiateCibilCheck(data)`, `verifyCibilOtp(otp, requestId)`.

